1
00:01:06,336 --> 00:01:10,778
=The Truth=

2
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:14,136
=Episode 24=

3
00:01:16,462 --> 00:01:17,262
Ning Haiyang!

4
00:01:22,822 --> 00:01:23,622
Don't worry.

5
00:01:30,223 --> 00:01:32,663
Ning Haiyang ran east
along the riverbank!

6
00:01:32,663 --> 00:01:33,262
After him!

7
00:01:41,023 --> 00:01:42,182
- Stop!
- Stop!

8
00:01:59,902 --> 00:02:00,542
What happened?

9
00:02:00,542 --> 00:02:01,303
You, go that way.

10
00:02:13,863 --> 00:02:14,423
Stop!

11
00:02:34,703 --> 00:02:35,182
Stop!

12
00:02:35,462 --> 00:02:36,342
- Stop!
- Stop!

13
00:02:36,502 --> 00:02:36,983
Stop!

14
00:02:58,062 --> 00:02:59,462
Over there! He's over there!

15
00:03:01,622 --> 00:03:03,062
- Stop!
- Stop!

16
00:03:04,502 --> 00:03:05,182
Stop!

17
00:03:16,342 --> 00:03:17,143
- Stop!
- That way!

18
00:03:17,383 --> 00:03:18,062
After him! Hurry!

19
00:03:37,942 --> 00:03:38,662
Stop!

20
00:03:40,502 --> 00:03:41,383
Stop!

21
00:03:55,383 --> 00:03:56,103
Go on, run.

22
00:03:56,942 --> 00:03:57,823
Keep running.

23
00:03:58,222 --> 00:03:59,143
Go on scaling the wall.

24
00:04:37,383 --> 00:04:37,982
Stop!

25
00:04:41,342 --> 00:04:41,943
Stop!

26
00:04:42,623 --> 00:04:43,943
- Stop!
- Still running?

27
00:04:45,183 --> 00:04:45,743
Stop!

28
00:04:46,422 --> 00:04:47,102
Give it up!

29
00:05:02,503 --> 00:05:03,063
Stay back!

30
00:05:03,263 --> 00:05:04,342
One more step, and I jump.

31
00:05:06,222 --> 00:05:07,102
Don't be rash.

32
00:05:07,462 --> 00:05:08,902
Don't be rash. Stay calm.

33
00:05:09,383 --> 00:05:10,743
Everyone step back.

34
00:05:12,982 --> 00:05:13,902
Easy. Take it easy.

35
00:05:13,902 --> 00:05:15,102
You won't survive that drop.

36
00:05:15,102 --> 00:05:15,662
It's too high.

37
00:05:16,302 --> 00:05:17,383
Don't underestimate me.

38
00:05:17,662 --> 00:05:19,342
Why would I underestimate you?

39
00:05:20,542 --> 00:05:23,023
I just think you are so young.

40
00:05:23,743 --> 00:05:25,823
What a tragedy it'd be if you fell.

41
00:05:26,263 --> 00:05:27,902
My life's worthless. No tragedy at all.

42
00:05:28,143 --> 00:05:29,063
Stay calm.

43
00:05:30,583 --> 00:05:32,982
You're here to see your mom, right?

44
00:05:33,823 --> 00:05:34,823
You're already here.

45
00:05:34,823 --> 00:05:36,302
Why not just meet her?

46
00:05:36,383 --> 00:05:37,383
Come over here. Come on.

47
00:05:37,383 --> 00:05:38,102
Don't move.

48
00:05:38,583 --> 00:05:39,982
Meeting her won't change anything.

49
00:05:40,143 --> 00:05:41,383
They've got new lives.

50
00:05:41,383 --> 00:05:42,143
New families.

51
00:05:42,383 --> 00:05:44,183
They don't want to see me
or care about me.

52
00:05:44,422 --> 00:05:46,143
Your mother's downstairs right now.

53
00:05:46,302 --> 00:05:47,102
Come over here.

54
00:05:47,302 --> 00:05:48,623
I'll take you to her. Come on.

55
00:05:48,823 --> 00:05:49,743
Stop lying.

56
00:05:50,263 --> 00:05:51,342
I'm not lying.

57
00:05:51,462 --> 00:05:52,462
See for yourself.

58
00:05:52,462 --> 00:05:53,503
She's right downstairs.

59
00:06:04,183 --> 00:06:05,222
That's not my mother.

60
00:06:05,263 --> 00:06:06,503
My real mother died long ago.

61
00:06:12,623 --> 00:06:14,422
Help! Help!

62
00:06:14,743 --> 00:06:15,422
Hurry! Help me!

63
00:06:15,422 --> 00:06:16,703
- Don't let go!
- Hold on!

64
00:06:18,503 --> 00:06:19,183
Help over here!

65
00:06:19,422 --> 00:06:20,222
Hold on tight!

66
00:06:20,703 --> 00:06:22,302
Stop struggling! Pull him up!

67
00:06:22,302 --> 00:06:22,862
Come on!

68
00:06:30,583 --> 00:06:31,342
Great work.

69
00:06:32,383 --> 00:06:33,183
Need to take this.

70
00:06:38,342 --> 00:06:38,943
Master.

71
00:06:41,982 --> 00:06:42,902
We found him.

72
00:06:46,743 --> 00:06:47,902
We also found Xiao Lan.

73
00:06:49,183 --> 00:06:50,902
Okay. Head back immediately.

74
00:07:31,902 --> 00:07:33,662
You're quite the window climber.

75
00:07:34,023 --> 00:07:34,862
Where'd you learn it?

76
00:07:36,063 --> 00:07:36,862
Martial arts school.

77
00:07:38,422 --> 00:07:39,503
Why'd you learn that?

78
00:07:40,143 --> 00:07:41,503
I never did well in school.

79
00:07:41,503 --> 00:07:42,862
Knew I wouldn't get into college.

80
00:07:43,183 --> 00:07:45,662
My mom worried I couldn't find a job

81
00:07:46,183 --> 00:07:47,302
and support myself.

82
00:07:49,143 --> 00:07:51,383
Your mom really thought it through.

83
00:07:52,302 --> 00:07:53,383
My dad died young.

84
00:07:53,902 --> 00:07:55,383
She could've remarried.

85
00:07:56,063 --> 00:07:57,183
But she had me to care for.

86
00:07:57,462 --> 00:07:58,542
So she never did.

87
00:07:59,342 --> 00:08:01,503
I knew I was adopted since childhood.

88
00:08:02,143 --> 00:08:04,063
But they always treated me well.

89
00:08:04,542 --> 00:08:07,063
I never wanted to leave
to find my real parents.

90
00:08:07,902 --> 00:08:09,102
Then my mom got sick.

91
00:08:09,662 --> 00:08:10,703
That's when she told me

92
00:08:10,902 --> 00:08:12,263
I was actually born in Renshan.

93
00:08:12,823 --> 00:08:15,462
She said I should find
my birth parents someday.

94
00:08:16,823 --> 00:08:20,183
So you went to Baijia Village
and found Bai Youfu's family.

95
00:08:22,943 --> 00:08:24,302
When I found them,

96
00:08:25,263 --> 00:08:27,623
they already had a family
and a new life.

97
00:08:28,383 --> 00:08:29,743
I didn't fit in at all.

98
00:08:30,743 --> 00:08:32,182
Your father said you threatened him.

99
00:08:33,062 --> 00:08:33,902
Is that true?

100
00:08:34,422 --> 00:08:35,223
Yeah.

101
00:08:35,662 --> 00:08:37,062
I threatened to call the police.

102
00:08:37,582 --> 00:08:38,782
That's when he told me

103
00:08:38,822 --> 00:08:40,182
who those two traffickers are.

104
00:08:40,343 --> 00:08:41,582
Why didn't you call the police?

105
00:08:49,302 --> 00:08:50,182
Do you know?

106
00:08:50,863 --> 00:08:53,702
We've been trying to catch them.

107
00:08:53,983 --> 00:08:55,822
They're wanted for many cases.

108
00:08:56,822 --> 00:08:59,302
Many families are waiting
for them to be caught,

109
00:08:59,542 --> 00:09:01,062
hoping to find their own children.

110
00:09:04,023 --> 00:09:05,263
I didn't mean to.

111
00:09:05,343 --> 00:09:06,662
I was just so angry.

112
00:09:07,103 --> 00:09:09,822
Those traffickers said
I wasn't taken away at all,

113
00:09:09,942 --> 00:09:11,582
but was sold by my own parents.

114
00:09:12,902 --> 00:09:14,343
I didn't believe it at first.

115
00:09:15,023 --> 00:09:17,463
So, when you ate in room 601
at the Rose Garden Hotel,

116
00:09:18,263 --> 00:09:20,062
was that before
or after you killed Liu Min?

117
00:09:22,422 --> 00:09:23,223
After.

118
00:09:23,743 --> 00:09:25,503
I'd been watching them for a long time.

119
00:09:25,782 --> 00:09:26,902
No time to eat.

120
00:09:27,623 --> 00:09:28,302
I was starving.

121
00:09:28,942 --> 00:09:31,582
Why send Liu Min and Liu Jianyuan's
phones to the police station?

122
00:09:33,463 --> 00:09:34,782
They were using fake identities.

123
00:09:35,263 --> 00:09:36,743
It'd be hard for you to catch them.

124
00:09:37,863 --> 00:09:39,302
I wanted to bring them to justice.

125
00:09:39,582 --> 00:09:40,702
Don't you get it?

126
00:09:41,822 --> 00:09:45,023
This kid's mind
is completely set on revenge.

127
00:09:45,542 --> 00:09:48,103
He probably hasn't even considered
the consequences.

128
00:09:49,302 --> 00:09:52,062
Ning Haiyang just turned 18.

129
00:09:52,702 --> 00:09:56,383
By law, 18 is an adult.

130
00:09:56,702 --> 00:09:59,582
Premeditated murder
could get him the death penalty.

131
00:09:59,623 --> 00:10:01,983
At the very least, life imprisonment.

132
00:10:02,463 --> 00:10:05,542
The victims in this case
are quite unique.

133
00:10:05,983 --> 00:10:07,422
Maybe he'll get a lighter sentence.

134
00:10:09,263 --> 00:10:11,582
A kid's sense of right and wrong
isn't fully developed.

135
00:10:12,263 --> 00:10:13,902
And he has no family around him.

136
00:10:15,822 --> 00:10:18,782
He's been lost on this journey
to find his family.

137
00:10:26,942 --> 00:10:28,582
Chang, almost done?

138
00:10:28,702 --> 00:10:30,422
Tell me what you want to eat later.

139
00:10:30,902 --> 00:10:31,743
Thank you, Ms. Jing.

140
00:10:36,383 --> 00:10:37,623
Is the food okay?

141
00:10:37,623 --> 00:10:38,983
Yeah, it's fine.

142
00:10:38,983 --> 00:10:39,743
Okay.

143
00:10:59,743 --> 00:11:01,302
Let me know if you want more dishes.

144
00:11:01,302 --> 00:11:02,143
- Got it!
- Okay!

145
00:11:04,863 --> 00:11:05,782
Everyone's here today.

146
00:11:05,782 --> 00:11:06,942
Is the case closed?

147
00:11:07,422 --> 00:11:10,263
I said I'd treat Master
once the case was wrapped up.

148
00:11:10,702 --> 00:11:11,623
It's still a way off.

149
00:11:11,623 --> 00:11:12,743
We ordered a lot. Dig in.

150
00:11:13,023 --> 00:11:13,863
Got reports to write.

151
00:11:16,103 --> 00:11:16,782
Come on.

152
00:11:16,902 --> 00:11:18,143
- Let's finish this.
- Good work, everyone.

153
00:11:18,143 --> 00:11:18,702
Yeah, good job.

154
00:11:18,702 --> 00:11:19,503
Let's toast.

155
00:11:20,582 --> 00:11:21,662
You okay here?

156
00:11:22,463 --> 00:11:23,383
I'm fine. It's nothing.

157
00:11:24,383 --> 00:11:28,062
(Dan Qing, why not reply to my message?)
I heard you almost lost that kid today.

158
00:11:30,182 --> 00:11:31,743
Why don't you try chasing him yourself?

159
00:11:36,143 --> 00:11:37,942
You just don't take kids
seriously enough.

160
00:11:38,662 --> 00:11:40,062
Kids these days are tough.

161
00:11:40,343 --> 00:11:41,143
Right, Xiaoyu?

162
00:11:45,503 --> 00:11:46,143
Eat.

163
00:11:47,343 --> 00:11:48,062
Stop playing.

164
00:11:48,902 --> 00:11:51,143
He's been on his phone
since we got here.

165
00:11:51,143 --> 00:11:52,143
Why don't you blame him?

166
00:11:53,662 --> 00:11:54,582
Stop playing.

167
00:11:54,983 --> 00:11:56,702
Set an example for Xiaoyu.

168
00:11:58,103 --> 00:11:59,023
Put it down.

169
00:11:59,103 --> 00:11:59,863
Anything happened?

170
00:11:59,863 --> 00:12:00,662
Go handle it.

171
00:12:00,662 --> 00:12:01,383
Anything happened?

172
00:12:02,503 --> 00:12:03,383
No, Master.

173
00:12:05,623 --> 00:12:08,302
Even selling your own child for profit

174
00:12:08,542 --> 00:12:09,782
is still child trafficking.

175
00:12:09,782 --> 00:12:10,743
It's still a crime.

176
00:12:11,542 --> 00:12:14,863
So shouldn't the child's real parents
be held legally responsible?

177
00:12:16,503 --> 00:12:17,983
The middleman is dead.

178
00:12:18,743 --> 00:12:20,902
The statute of limitations has expired.

179
00:12:27,743 --> 00:12:28,383
Gao!

180
00:12:28,383 --> 00:12:29,542
- Call an ambulance!
- Call an ambulance!

181
00:12:29,902 --> 00:12:30,942
- Gao!
- What's happening?

182
00:12:31,503 --> 00:12:33,182
Hello? This is No-Name Diner.

183
00:12:34,023 --> 00:12:35,182
Step back, everyone.

184
00:12:35,182 --> 00:12:36,343
Someone's fainted. Come now!

185
00:12:36,343 --> 00:12:37,463
What happened?

186
00:12:37,623 --> 00:12:39,103
Call an ambulance! Hurry up!

187
00:12:39,542 --> 00:12:40,343
Did someone call?

188
00:12:40,343 --> 00:12:40,983
It's done.

189
00:12:41,103 --> 00:12:42,103
You called?

190
00:12:42,143 --> 00:12:42,743
I don't know.

191
00:12:42,743 --> 00:12:43,983
He just collapsed suddenly.

192
00:12:43,983 --> 00:12:45,902
- How much did he drink?
- Does he need CPR?

193
00:12:45,902 --> 00:12:47,782
- He didn't drink.
- Didn't he? Then how...

194
00:12:48,623 --> 00:12:49,302
Be careful.

195
00:12:51,863 --> 00:12:52,383
Take it slow.

196
00:12:53,422 --> 00:12:54,182
Slowly.

197
00:12:54,702 --> 00:12:55,463
Lift him up.

198
00:12:56,343 --> 00:12:57,343
Help lift from inside.

199
00:13:00,302 --> 00:13:00,983
Huang, you go.

200
00:13:01,463 --> 00:13:02,143
You may leave.

201
00:13:08,302 --> 00:13:09,343
Call his wife.

202
00:13:09,582 --> 00:13:10,223
Okay.

203
00:13:14,343 --> 00:13:15,863
Master, I'll take them to hospital.

204
00:13:17,582 --> 00:13:18,383
Take it easy.

205
00:13:19,062 --> 00:13:20,182
Go. I'll take you there.

206
00:13:20,182 --> 00:13:21,112
Thanks, Captain Leng.

207
00:13:23,582 --> 00:13:26,702
Gao isn't even 50 yet, is he?

208
00:13:26,983 --> 00:13:28,383
Cardiovascular issues already?

209
00:13:29,143 --> 00:13:30,662
Fortunately, it was caught in time.

210
00:13:30,942 --> 00:13:32,383
His daughter's taking the exam.

211
00:13:36,302 --> 00:13:38,702
Police work is inherently high-pressure.

212
00:13:38,942 --> 00:13:41,863
Especially in their unit, where tasks
are heavy and deadlines tight.

213
00:13:42,182 --> 00:13:44,182
But someone's got to do this job, right?

214
00:13:45,422 --> 00:13:46,822
Don't ever eat pork chops.

215
00:13:46,822 --> 00:13:48,062
- I won't.
- Cardiovascular disease.

216
00:13:48,623 --> 00:13:49,422
I know.

217
00:13:49,422 --> 00:13:50,023
Let's go.

218
00:13:50,023 --> 00:13:51,302
Don't worry.

219
00:13:51,302 --> 00:13:52,383
No problem.

220
00:13:56,389 --> 00:14:00,024
(No-Name Diner)

221
00:14:21,983 --> 00:14:22,942
Right over there.

222
00:14:24,223 --> 00:14:25,023
- Ye, thank you.
- Ye.

223
00:14:25,023 --> 00:14:25,623
Thank you.

224
00:14:25,743 --> 00:14:26,902
Qian, thank you

225
00:14:26,902 --> 00:14:28,223
for staying here so late.

226
00:14:28,542 --> 00:14:28,983
How is he?

227
00:14:28,983 --> 00:14:29,542
Busy all day.

228
00:14:29,542 --> 00:14:30,503
Go get some rest.

229
00:14:30,743 --> 00:14:31,422
- Thanks.
- Okay.

230
00:14:31,422 --> 00:14:32,503
He'll be fine. Don't worry.

231
00:14:32,863 --> 00:14:33,422
Okay.

232
00:14:33,422 --> 00:14:34,223
How is he?

233
00:14:34,422 --> 00:14:35,463
In the emergency room.

234
00:14:37,463 --> 00:14:38,383
The doctor's here.

235
00:14:39,223 --> 00:14:40,743
Doctor, how is he?

236
00:14:40,902 --> 00:14:41,743
Nothing too serious.

237
00:14:41,782 --> 00:14:42,702
Doctor, doctor.

238
00:15:02,584 --> 00:15:04,280
(Dan Qing)

239
00:15:31,062 --> 00:15:31,623
Come on.

240
00:15:38,182 --> 00:15:38,902
Take a look.

241
00:15:44,702 --> 00:15:46,582
This is your grandpa's room.

242
00:15:47,143 --> 00:15:48,263
Haven't tidied it up much.

243
00:15:48,263 --> 00:15:49,702
I'll sleep in here tonight.

244
00:15:50,623 --> 00:15:52,263
My room has been cleaned up.

245
00:15:53,023 --> 00:15:53,743
You sleep there.

246
00:15:55,103 --> 00:15:55,702
Come.

247
00:16:02,343 --> 00:16:03,143
Hungry?

248
00:16:03,263 --> 00:16:04,062
Kind of.

249
00:16:05,103 --> 00:16:07,062
If you're not hungry, skip eating.

250
00:16:07,902 --> 00:16:08,702
Lose some weight.

251
00:16:11,503 --> 00:16:13,383
Actually, I quite like Ms. Ziwu.

252
00:16:15,782 --> 00:16:16,863
I mean

253
00:16:16,863 --> 00:16:18,702
I wouldn't mind if you married her.

254
00:16:18,942 --> 00:16:22,822
What's that little head of yours
pondering every day?

255
00:16:25,942 --> 00:16:27,822
If I were her,
I definitely wouldn't choose you.

256
00:16:28,182 --> 00:16:28,983
What do you mean?

257
00:16:29,343 --> 00:16:31,302
You think she looks down on me?

258
00:16:31,822 --> 00:16:32,942
That's not what I meant.

259
00:16:34,822 --> 00:16:35,863
How's your mom?

260
00:16:36,623 --> 00:16:37,542
She's alright.

261
00:16:38,103 --> 00:16:41,302
Does she talk about me often with you?

262
00:16:46,302 --> 00:16:48,062
Can't we just see you on TV?

263
00:16:48,463 --> 00:16:49,463
What's that talk?

264
00:17:42,712 --> 00:17:46,205
♪Replacing the weight of tears
with that of sweat♪

265
00:17:49,999 --> 00:17:55,320
♪Covering the gunshot's sound
with wounds♪

266
00:17:57,393 --> 00:18:02,247
♪No one is born unyielding and strong♪

267
00:18:03,053 --> 00:18:06,200
♪But because someone
always rushes ahead♪

268
00:18:06,200 --> 00:18:09,304
♪To shield us from the storm♪

269
00:18:11,960 --> 00:18:17,094
♪When every extraordinary act
becomes routine♪

270
00:18:19,064 --> 00:18:24,696
♪Just to polish the badge
upon their shoulder♪

271
00:18:26,456 --> 00:18:30,040
♪Like light surging unseen
through the night♪

272
00:18:31,192 --> 00:18:37,782
♪Converging into your form♪

273
00:18:37,782 --> 00:18:38,582
Hello, Mr. Zhao.

274
00:18:39,263 --> 00:18:40,503
Sorry to disturb you so late.

275
00:18:40,782 --> 00:18:41,582
Ye Qian,

276
00:18:42,062 --> 00:18:44,102
I know what you're calling to ask.

277
00:18:44,463 --> 00:18:47,382
What I can tell you now is
the big fish has bitten.

278
00:18:47,542 --> 00:18:49,503
Your mission is complete.

279
00:18:49,622 --> 00:18:51,943
No further involvement
is needed from you.

280
00:18:55,102 --> 00:18:55,622
Okay.

281
00:18:56,276 --> 00:19:00,760
♪Alone, they charge ahead♪

282
00:19:00,760 --> 00:19:03,576
♪Traversing♪

283
00:19:03,576 --> 00:19:08,952
♪The battlefield of fate♪

284
00:19:14,342 --> 00:19:15,703
Grandpa misses you a lot.

285
00:19:16,463 --> 00:19:19,302
But the hospital
isn't allowing visitors lately.

286
00:19:19,743 --> 00:19:20,622
Next time.

287
00:19:20,983 --> 00:19:22,542
Alright, next time.

288
00:19:23,862 --> 00:19:26,943
Lately, I've been pretty busy too.

289
00:19:26,943 --> 00:19:28,102
Not much time spent with you.

290
00:19:29,223 --> 00:19:30,062
You okay?

291
00:19:30,862 --> 00:19:32,703
It's fine. I'll come again
during summer break.

292
00:19:33,342 --> 00:19:34,023
Okay.

293
00:19:41,302 --> 00:19:41,943
Eat.

294
00:19:42,782 --> 00:19:45,102
Mr. Long lost at video games
and can't accept losing to me,

295
00:19:45,102 --> 00:19:46,382
saying he'll beat me next time.

296
00:19:46,382 --> 00:19:47,142
Is that so?

297
00:19:47,862 --> 00:19:48,862
He's not bad at gaming.

298
00:19:53,463 --> 00:19:55,023
How's that uncle from last night?

299
00:19:55,822 --> 00:19:56,463
He's okay.

300
00:19:57,342 --> 00:19:58,183
He's fine?

301
00:20:02,503 --> 00:20:04,582
(Welcome to today's Legal Report.)

302
00:20:04,582 --> 00:20:06,862
(Regarding the Ning murder case
that occurred recently,)

303
00:20:06,862 --> 00:20:08,862
(after extensive searches
by the police,)

304
00:20:08,862 --> 00:20:10,183
(the suspect was apprehended.)

305
00:20:10,183 --> 00:20:11,743
(Due to a child trafficking incident,)

306
00:20:11,743 --> 00:20:12,983
(Ning intended to kill.)

307
00:20:12,983 --> 00:20:14,503
(Details follow.)

308
00:20:15,342 --> 00:20:18,102
(In this arrest operation,)

309
00:20:18,382 --> 00:20:23,943
(through the joint efforts
of Yunxi CID's captain and officers,)

310
00:20:23,943 --> 00:20:28,023
(CID carried out surveillance
and apprehension measures)

311
00:20:28,023 --> 00:20:31,102
(while ensuring public safety.
Braving personal risk,)

312
00:20:31,223 --> 00:20:34,023
(they apprehended
the suspect, Ning, to justice.)

313
00:20:53,062 --> 00:20:53,903
Have a steamed bun.

314
00:20:54,102 --> 00:20:54,936
Have a steamed bun.

315
00:21:06,463 --> 00:21:08,542
Dad, work's been busy.

316
00:21:08,542 --> 00:21:09,503
Take care of yourself.

317
00:21:09,503 --> 00:21:10,542
See you next month.

318
00:21:17,663 --> 00:21:18,302
Okay.

319
00:21:19,503 --> 00:21:20,663
Thanks, son.

320
00:21:21,503 --> 00:21:24,302
You need to focus on your studies too.

321
00:21:25,782 --> 00:21:26,862
Get plenty of exercise.

322
00:21:28,582 --> 00:21:29,862
Take good care of your mom.

323
00:21:31,542 --> 00:21:32,782
Don't make her angry.

324
00:21:34,102 --> 00:21:34,903
Remember that.

325
00:21:34,903 --> 00:21:35,423
I will.

326
00:21:35,423 --> 00:21:36,463
Play fewer video games.

327
00:21:39,822 --> 00:21:40,703
- It's almost time.
- You should get going.

328
00:21:41,503 --> 00:21:42,183
Xiaoyu.

329
00:21:42,983 --> 00:21:44,703
Take a steamed bun.

330
00:21:44,703 --> 00:21:45,382
- Thanks, ma'am.
- for the road.

331
00:21:45,382 --> 00:21:46,542
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

332
00:21:46,542 --> 00:21:47,142
Okay.

333
00:21:47,622 --> 00:21:48,423
Thanks.

334
00:21:49,703 --> 00:21:51,782
Could you pack this up for us later?

335
00:21:51,943 --> 00:21:53,102
Okay, I'll take care of it.

336
00:21:53,223 --> 00:21:53,862
Goodbye, ma'am.

337
00:21:53,862 --> 00:21:54,703
Take care.

338
00:21:57,720 --> 00:22:00,472
(Yunxi Police Department)

339
00:22:04,983 --> 00:22:06,582
It's been several days now.

340
00:22:08,503 --> 00:22:10,023
She hasn't replied to my messages.

341
00:22:10,023 --> 00:22:11,463
I wonder how she's doing there.

342
00:22:12,782 --> 00:22:14,503
Maybe she just doesn't want
to talk to you?

343
00:22:16,183 --> 00:22:16,983
Impossible.

344
00:22:18,782 --> 00:22:21,223
Could it be that Little Zhao
attracted someone's attention

345
00:22:21,223 --> 00:22:23,183
as soon as she got there?

346
00:22:23,703 --> 00:22:24,542
Could be!

347
00:22:25,142 --> 00:22:28,023
I'm worried she might run
into bad people.

348
00:22:29,703 --> 00:22:31,263
What if she met her true love?

349
00:22:32,142 --> 00:22:34,023
I'm her true love, okay?

350
00:22:37,102 --> 00:22:37,903
Captain Leng.

351
00:22:38,622 --> 00:22:39,423
Master.

352
00:22:47,062 --> 00:22:49,062
Ever seen Captain Leng like this?

353
00:22:51,183 --> 00:22:52,023
Never.

354
00:22:54,943 --> 00:22:56,263
Did he win the lottery?

355
00:22:59,342 --> 00:23:00,142
I'll go ask.

356
00:23:03,822 --> 00:23:04,463
Captain Leng.

357
00:23:06,023 --> 00:23:07,302
What's got you so happy?

358
00:23:07,703 --> 00:23:09,023
Mind your own business.

359
00:23:12,542 --> 00:23:13,503
Get back to work.

360
00:23:19,992 --> 00:23:23,123
(No-Name Diner)

361
00:24:03,743 --> 00:24:04,382
Come on.

362
00:24:05,943 --> 00:24:06,503
Come on.

363
00:24:11,342 --> 00:24:11,983
Alright.

364
00:24:12,223 --> 00:24:13,423
I'll make another batch.

365
00:24:21,983 --> 00:24:23,382
You're picking this up fast!

366
00:24:25,943 --> 00:24:26,782
Come on.

367
00:24:33,582 --> 00:24:35,023
Careful, don't spill it.

368
00:24:35,223 --> 00:24:35,862
It's fine.

369
00:24:35,862 --> 00:24:36,663
I'm off.

370
00:24:36,663 --> 00:24:37,223
Alright!

371
00:24:37,542 --> 00:24:38,062
Bye-bye.

372
00:24:38,062 --> 00:24:38,582
Take care.

373
00:24:43,142 --> 00:24:44,983
Got it. See you tomorrow!

374
00:24:46,263 --> 00:24:47,223
You've worked hard.

375
00:24:47,223 --> 00:24:47,743
Bye!

376
00:24:54,264 --> 00:24:59,352
(No-Name Diner)

377
00:25:00,062 --> 00:25:00,542
Here.

378
00:25:00,542 --> 00:25:01,142
Come on.

379
00:25:01,223 --> 00:25:01,943
Three lunch boxes.

380
00:25:01,943 --> 00:25:02,822
- Thank you.
- Much appreciated.

381
00:25:02,822 --> 00:25:03,503
Thanks.

382
00:25:03,503 --> 00:25:05,142
- Share them.
- Help yourselves.

383
00:25:05,142 --> 00:25:06,223
Chopsticks.

384
00:25:06,223 --> 00:25:07,183
Here you go. Okay.

385
00:25:07,183 --> 00:25:08,183
- I got it.
- Okay.

386
00:25:08,183 --> 00:25:08,703
Thanks a lot.

387
00:25:08,703 --> 00:25:09,382
Take your time.

388
00:25:09,423 --> 00:25:10,782
- Okay.
- Thanks for the hard work.

389
00:25:10,782 --> 00:25:11,223
Thank you.

390
00:25:11,943 --> 00:25:13,663
Come on, Qian.

391
00:25:13,663 --> 00:25:14,782
Let's eat.

392
00:25:17,142 --> 00:25:17,822
Come on.

393
00:25:18,023 --> 00:25:19,142
Thanks.

394
00:25:32,542 --> 00:25:34,582
Remember what I told you before?

395
00:25:36,342 --> 00:25:38,463
Times like this always
make me really happy.

396
00:25:38,463 --> 00:25:39,582
Know why?

397
00:25:42,663 --> 00:25:45,903
It's that joy of helping others.

398
00:25:45,903 --> 00:25:49,023
That sense of accomplishment
money can't buy.

399
00:25:50,302 --> 00:25:53,023
I just want a simple life every day.

400
00:25:53,862 --> 00:25:55,423
With family, with friends,

401
00:25:56,142 --> 00:25:57,663
with work I enjoy,

402
00:25:59,102 --> 00:25:59,943
with brothers,

403
00:26:00,622 --> 00:26:01,423
that's enough.

404
00:26:07,223 --> 00:26:09,862
You asked me once
if being a cop makes me happy.

405
00:26:14,703 --> 00:26:15,943
Speaking of happiness,

406
00:26:16,423 --> 00:26:17,023
there is.

407
00:26:17,903 --> 00:26:21,102
But more importantly,
it gives me a sense of purpose.

408
00:26:23,703 --> 00:26:24,503
How so?

409
00:26:26,862 --> 00:26:28,183
Every time I catch a criminal,

410
00:26:29,782 --> 00:26:33,102
it makes me believe
I'm changing something.

411
00:26:34,542 --> 00:26:35,542
Maybe it's the people.

412
00:26:36,903 --> 00:26:37,903
Maybe it's situations.

413
00:26:40,622 --> 00:26:45,223
I always think if I work harder,

414
00:26:46,663 --> 00:26:48,622
fewer tragedies would happen,

415
00:26:49,983 --> 00:26:52,023
and the world might become
a better place.

416
00:26:57,983 --> 00:27:00,703
You really have
a strong sense of mission.

417
00:27:01,102 --> 00:27:02,263
You're right.

418
00:27:02,263 --> 00:27:03,903
It's just that some things...

419
00:27:04,062 --> 00:27:05,943
Once you have a goal and then act,

420
00:27:05,943 --> 00:27:07,463
the outcome might be different.

421
00:27:07,703 --> 00:27:08,703
It depends on what we do.

422
00:27:08,703 --> 00:27:09,423
Cheers.

423
00:27:31,622 --> 00:27:32,582
I'm so scared.

424
00:27:32,582 --> 00:27:34,302
What happened? How did he get killed?

425
00:27:34,622 --> 00:27:37,142
Heard it was a man from building 8.

426
00:27:37,142 --> 00:27:38,822
Usually, his wife and kids
aren't around.

427
00:27:38,822 --> 00:27:40,023
He lived alone.

428
00:27:40,023 --> 00:27:41,223
Do you know how he died?

429
00:27:41,423 --> 00:27:43,983
They say debt collectors broke in
and hacked him to death.

430
00:27:43,983 --> 00:27:44,983
How awful.

431
00:27:44,983 --> 00:27:46,102
Just gone like that.

432
00:27:46,102 --> 00:27:47,223
In broad daylight.

433
00:27:47,223 --> 00:27:48,023
Exactly.

434
00:27:57,503 --> 00:27:58,423
- Captain Leng.
- Captain Leng.

435
00:27:59,062 --> 00:27:59,663
How is it?

436
00:27:59,663 --> 00:28:00,263
What happened?

437
00:28:00,423 --> 00:28:02,862
Via property management,
we found the deceased was Zhao Sihui.

438
00:28:02,903 --> 00:28:04,503
Nicknamed Zhao Heizi, aged 55.

439
00:28:04,862 --> 00:28:07,102
He lived alone in room 208, building 8.

440
00:28:07,142 --> 00:28:08,822
His daughter married
to Shanghai in 2020.

441
00:28:09,142 --> 00:28:10,903
His wife also went
to Shanghai a year later.

442
00:28:10,903 --> 00:28:12,663
We've notified his daughter to return.

443
00:28:13,102 --> 00:28:15,862
Additionally,
our neighborhood canvass revealed

444
00:28:15,862 --> 00:28:17,183
that he had a poor reputation.

445
00:28:17,183 --> 00:28:18,503
Debt collectors often came.

446
00:28:18,782 --> 00:28:19,822
According to a neighbor,

447
00:28:19,822 --> 00:28:22,102
she heard loud knocking this morning,

448
00:28:22,183 --> 00:28:24,302
but was too scared to go check.

449
00:28:24,503 --> 00:28:25,503
When she looked out,

450
00:28:25,503 --> 00:28:27,023
she found the door opposite wide open.

451
00:28:27,983 --> 00:28:31,223
She went inside
and discovered Zhao Sihui murdered,

452
00:28:31,223 --> 00:28:32,183
lying in blood.

453
00:28:32,183 --> 00:28:33,263
So she called the police.

454
00:28:33,342 --> 00:28:34,663
Is the scene sampling done?

455
00:28:34,743 --> 00:28:35,663
Yes.

456
00:28:42,822 --> 00:28:43,503
Quickly!

457
00:28:46,542 --> 00:28:47,302
Which floor?

458
00:28:47,382 --> 00:28:48,663
Second floor. Ahead.

459
00:28:49,142 --> 00:28:49,663
Master.

460
00:28:49,983 --> 00:28:50,423
Hurry.

461
00:28:52,302 --> 00:28:53,102
Homicide.

462
00:28:54,142 --> 00:28:55,862
Heard there's blood everywhere
in the room.

463
00:28:55,862 --> 00:28:57,382
I will lose sleep tonight.

464
00:28:57,903 --> 00:28:59,023
Exactly.

465
00:28:59,023 --> 00:29:00,062
Well, this is just great.

466
00:29:00,062 --> 00:29:00,703
Who knows?

467
00:29:00,703 --> 00:29:02,582
Will this affect our property values?

468
00:29:02,582 --> 00:29:04,342
Why did we have to get
this awful trouble?

469
00:29:48,382 --> 00:29:49,503
Single perpetrator.

470
00:29:55,342 --> 00:29:56,503
Based on footprints,

471
00:29:57,542 --> 00:29:58,263
it appears so.

472
00:30:22,263 --> 00:30:22,822
This room.

473
00:30:25,943 --> 00:30:26,582
Captain Leng.

474
00:30:40,503 --> 00:30:41,183
Any findings?

475
00:30:47,423 --> 00:30:49,062
The deceased was wearing leather shoes.

476
00:30:49,903 --> 00:30:51,542
Slippers were still on the rack.

477
00:30:51,983 --> 00:30:55,782
Normally, he'd change
into slippers upon entering.

478
00:30:56,463 --> 00:30:58,782
So he hadn't changed yet

479
00:30:59,542 --> 00:31:00,983
when the killer attacked.

480
00:31:02,142 --> 00:31:04,463
The killer either followed him in

481
00:31:05,663 --> 00:31:07,582
or was waiting inside.

482
00:31:16,223 --> 00:31:18,023
A kitchen knife is missing.

483
00:31:19,183 --> 00:31:20,463
Its pattern matches this one.

484
00:31:22,782 --> 00:31:27,463
The suspect definitely
took this knife from the kitchen.

485
00:31:28,582 --> 00:31:29,582
Look, Ye.

486
00:31:30,943 --> 00:31:33,463
See these neck wounds?

487
00:31:34,542 --> 00:31:38,463
Suspect must have struck twice
at the neck.

488
00:31:39,622 --> 00:31:43,183
Blood spatter concentrated here too,

489
00:31:44,382 --> 00:31:45,582
though less volume.

490
00:31:46,582 --> 00:31:50,903
If the suspect attacked from behind,

491
00:31:50,903 --> 00:31:52,263
catching him off guard,

492
00:31:52,263 --> 00:31:55,582
the spatter pattern
wouldn't look like this.

493
00:31:55,903 --> 00:31:57,703
This indicates

494
00:31:57,703 --> 00:32:01,023
the suspect faced the victim
during the attack.

495
00:32:01,822 --> 00:32:02,862
According to my analysis,

496
00:32:03,102 --> 00:32:03,983
two possibilities.

497
00:32:04,822 --> 00:32:05,622
First,

498
00:32:07,342 --> 00:32:09,703
personal grudge.

499
00:32:10,903 --> 00:32:12,862
Suspect lay in wait

500
00:32:12,862 --> 00:32:13,943
and seized the opportunity.

501
00:32:14,342 --> 00:32:16,822
Or they were strangers.

502
00:32:18,382 --> 00:32:19,822
During the crime,

503
00:32:19,822 --> 00:32:21,342
suspect was discovered,

504
00:32:22,703 --> 00:32:24,663
so he killed and fled.

505
00:32:24,943 --> 00:32:29,423
But we need to verify all this.

506
00:32:30,382 --> 00:32:31,023
Wang Tong,

507
00:32:31,382 --> 00:32:34,743
examine the victim's connections
as soon as possible.

508
00:32:36,782 --> 00:32:37,582
Ye,

509
00:32:38,023 --> 00:32:39,183
take Liu Yang

510
00:32:40,183 --> 00:32:44,382
and identify the two individuals
at the scene this morning.

511
00:32:45,223 --> 00:32:48,423
We can't proceed without this.

512
00:32:48,582 --> 00:32:49,183
Yes.

513
00:32:49,503 --> 00:32:50,663
Get moving! Fast!

514
00:33:04,423 --> 00:33:05,622
Shanzai, Haozi.

515
00:33:05,862 --> 00:33:06,822
I-I'm here.

516
00:33:07,703 --> 00:33:09,183
We're from Yunxi Police Department.

517
00:33:09,862 --> 00:33:11,023
Here are our credentials.

518
00:33:14,423 --> 00:33:16,183
You're here for Zhao Heizi, right?

519
00:33:17,142 --> 00:33:21,703
Witnesses say you went to Building 8,
Lvyin Community for Zhao Heizi today.

520
00:33:22,223 --> 00:33:23,582
We did go there.

521
00:33:23,582 --> 00:33:25,622
But when we arrived,
he was already dead.

522
00:33:26,102 --> 00:33:26,943
How did you find him?

523
00:33:27,302 --> 00:33:29,822
I-I pried the door open.

524
00:33:29,822 --> 00:33:31,983
H-He was lying right there
when I entered.

525
00:33:34,102 --> 00:33:35,183
Come with us.

526
00:33:35,183 --> 00:33:36,183
Please cooperate.

527
00:33:41,782 --> 00:33:42,423
Officer,

528
00:33:43,302 --> 00:33:44,382
I know the drill.

529
00:33:44,903 --> 00:33:47,263
But we really didn't kill him.

530
00:33:48,423 --> 00:33:50,862
We're willing to cooperate
with the police investigation.

531
00:33:51,943 --> 00:33:53,822
Yes, we're very willing.

532
00:33:54,342 --> 00:33:55,183
Absolutely willing.

533
00:33:56,183 --> 00:33:56,983
Take them in.

534
00:33:57,903 --> 00:33:58,703
Follow me.

535
00:34:03,382 --> 00:34:04,183
Get in the back.

536
00:34:12,903 --> 00:34:13,702
Come inside.

537
00:34:15,943 --> 00:34:16,823
Have a seat.

538
00:34:29,783 --> 00:34:31,262
You know the situation already.

539
00:34:31,823 --> 00:34:32,863
Zhao Heizi is dead.

540
00:34:33,582 --> 00:34:35,262
We need your cooperation.

541
00:34:35,823 --> 00:34:38,303
Tell us everything you know.

542
00:34:38,783 --> 00:34:39,742
I'll cooperate fully.

543
00:34:39,742 --> 00:34:41,222
I'll give you my full cooperation.

544
00:34:42,463 --> 00:34:44,023
Did you know Zhao Heizi well?

545
00:34:44,423 --> 00:34:45,622
I knew him fairly well.

546
00:34:46,222 --> 00:34:48,383
He was notoriously addicted to gambling.

547
00:34:50,582 --> 00:34:51,222
Go on.

548
00:34:52,062 --> 00:34:53,262
Speaking of Zhao Heizi,

549
00:34:53,262 --> 00:34:54,463
he was a lucky man.

550
00:34:54,662 --> 00:34:56,662
His daughter was his personal cash cow.

551
00:34:57,023 --> 00:34:59,823
Otherwise, he'd have starved years ago.

552
00:35:00,062 --> 00:35:00,983
Get to the point.

553
00:35:02,463 --> 00:35:04,863
About six or seven years back,

554
00:35:04,863 --> 00:35:06,983
I met him during a card game
with friends.

555
00:35:07,222 --> 00:35:08,702
He was gambling heavily back then.

556
00:35:08,983 --> 00:35:10,343
He'd show up in every card game.

557
00:35:10,903 --> 00:35:12,062
Was Zhao Heizi wealthy?

558
00:35:12,463 --> 00:35:13,262
Him?

559
00:35:13,783 --> 00:35:16,383
How could a laid-off worker
have that kind of money?

560
00:35:16,662 --> 00:35:18,182
It all came from his daughter.

561
00:35:18,542 --> 00:35:20,023
His daughter was stunning.

562
00:35:20,423 --> 00:35:23,343
Rumor says she married
some rich southern businessman.

563
00:35:23,662 --> 00:35:26,343
Bought multiple properties
right here in Yunxi City alone.

564
00:35:26,863 --> 00:35:28,423
How do you know all this?

565
00:35:28,943 --> 00:35:30,662
Zhao Heizi bragged about it himself.

566
00:35:34,142 --> 00:35:35,983
Because of his gambling,

567
00:35:36,182 --> 00:35:39,622
his wife and daughter got fed up
and moved to Shanghai,

568
00:35:39,983 --> 00:35:41,423
leaving him here all alone.

569
00:35:42,262 --> 00:35:44,943
So how did he support himself?

570
00:35:45,903 --> 00:35:48,582
His daughter sent him
a few thousand yuan monthly.

571
00:35:49,343 --> 00:35:50,823
She also left him several properties.

572
00:35:51,222 --> 00:35:53,343
But the deeds were all in her name.

573
00:35:53,702 --> 00:35:55,142
So he couldn't sell them.

574
00:35:55,222 --> 00:35:57,742
He could just rent them out
for pocket money.

575
00:35:58,662 --> 00:36:01,823
The rest was decided by fate.

576
00:36:03,542 --> 00:36:04,463
Decided by fate?

577
00:36:05,222 --> 00:36:08,142
Playing Pai Gow, betting on dice rolls.

578
00:36:08,343 --> 00:36:10,182
Winning or losing was up to fate.

579
00:36:11,032 --> 00:36:16,521
(Hongfa Mahjong Parlor)

580
00:36:17,783 --> 00:36:19,343
Heizi, you're leaving?

581
00:36:35,128 --> 00:36:38,721
(Haibo Finance)

582
00:36:47,503 --> 00:36:48,303
Shanzai.

583
00:36:48,542 --> 00:36:49,983
What's Uncle Bo's word?

584
00:36:51,222 --> 00:36:54,463
He said to tag along with you.

585
00:36:54,983 --> 00:36:55,783
Got it.

586
00:36:56,343 --> 00:36:58,582
But did Uncle Bo mention anything

587
00:36:58,823 --> 00:36:59,983
about the money?

588
00:37:00,222 --> 00:37:01,863
Wait, sir, don't get me wrong.

589
00:37:01,863 --> 00:37:03,783
I know Uncle Bo always treats me right.

590
00:37:03,783 --> 00:37:05,542
I rushed over the second
I heard the news.

591
00:37:05,783 --> 00:37:07,943
Thinking I'd help Uncle Bo
collect that debt fast.

592
00:37:08,503 --> 00:37:09,742
Relax.

593
00:37:09,783 --> 00:37:11,783
Would Uncle Bo ever short you?

594
00:37:12,222 --> 00:37:13,222
Uncle Bo's orders are

595
00:37:13,222 --> 00:37:16,742
collecting the money,
and then following standard procedure.

596
00:37:17,503 --> 00:37:19,503
Gimme a minute. Got some business first.

597
00:37:19,823 --> 00:37:21,503
I need to handle something real quick.

598
00:37:22,262 --> 00:37:23,222
We'll head over later.

599
00:37:23,222 --> 00:37:24,062
Wait for my word.

600
00:37:24,903 --> 00:37:25,423
Okay, sir.

601
00:37:25,423 --> 00:37:26,062
You go ahead.

602
00:37:26,062 --> 00:37:26,943
Okay.

603
00:37:27,423 --> 00:37:28,023
Okay.

604
00:37:28,182 --> 00:37:28,702
Alright!

605
00:37:33,503 --> 00:37:36,983
So you were after him to collect a debt?

606
00:37:37,463 --> 00:37:40,823
Zhao Heizi borrowed 100 thousand
from Uncle Bo last month.

607
00:37:41,863 --> 00:37:43,823
He hasn't paid back a single cent since.

608
00:37:44,062 --> 00:37:46,383
Haozi told us

609
00:37:46,742 --> 00:37:48,823
that he won a lot yesterday
and sent us to collect.

610
00:37:49,943 --> 00:37:52,182
Getting that would clear his debt.

611
00:37:53,983 --> 00:37:56,742
Do you know who else
he owed money besides you?

612
00:37:57,983 --> 00:38:00,823
It was his first time
borrowing from Uncle Bo.

613
00:38:01,702 --> 00:38:05,383
We heard he had multiple creditors.

614
00:38:05,823 --> 00:38:08,303
His daughter covered
a lot of it already.

615
00:38:08,702 --> 00:38:10,622
So you fronted him the cash.

616
00:38:14,023 --> 00:38:16,662
Uncle Bo gave the green light.

617
00:38:17,662 --> 00:38:18,182
Sir,

618
00:38:18,582 --> 00:38:20,383
what if he won't open the door later?

619
00:38:20,662 --> 00:38:21,383
Won't open?

620
00:38:21,783 --> 00:38:23,343
If he doesn't open, we'll pry it open.

621
00:38:24,463 --> 00:38:25,182
Okay.

622
00:38:26,863 --> 00:38:27,983
Wait, sir.

623
00:38:28,142 --> 00:38:30,062
He... Zhao Heizi knows me.

624
00:38:30,062 --> 00:38:31,463
This won't cause trouble, right?

625
00:38:31,463 --> 00:38:31,983
What trouble?

626
00:38:32,463 --> 00:38:33,702
What's he going to do to you?

627
00:38:34,542 --> 00:38:35,343
Afraid of what?

628
00:38:36,582 --> 00:38:38,783
Paying debts is only right and proper.

629
00:38:39,303 --> 00:38:40,542
Be smart later.

630
00:38:41,343 --> 00:38:43,943
Just learn how to talk

631
00:38:44,783 --> 00:38:45,582
and handle things.

632
00:38:45,742 --> 00:38:46,383
Okay.

633
00:38:48,463 --> 00:38:50,023
Know the unit number?

634
00:38:50,463 --> 00:38:52,343
Yes. His place is 208.

635
00:38:52,983 --> 00:38:53,783
You've been here?

636
00:38:53,943 --> 00:38:55,463
No, it's my first time too.

637
00:38:55,463 --> 00:38:56,542
A friend told me.

638
00:38:57,262 --> 00:38:58,423
He loves gambling, right?

639
00:38:58,423 --> 00:39:00,142
He's superstitious about numbers

640
00:39:00,142 --> 00:39:01,222
like 66 or 88.

641
00:39:01,222 --> 00:39:02,542
What 66 and 88?

642
00:39:02,542 --> 00:39:03,582
He's just a gambler.

643
00:39:03,943 --> 00:39:05,582
If the money isn't paid,

644
00:39:06,142 --> 00:39:06,903
he's dead.

645
00:39:07,423 --> 00:39:08,702
Okay. Dead.

646
00:39:18,343 --> 00:39:19,983
Sir, here.

647
00:39:27,983 --> 00:39:28,783
Zhao Heizi!

648
00:39:30,903 --> 00:39:32,343
Paying back the money or not?

649
00:39:34,582 --> 00:39:36,062
Playing dead in there, huh?

650
00:39:36,983 --> 00:39:39,142
Say something, or we're coming in!

651
00:39:40,062 --> 00:39:40,702
Sir,

652
00:39:40,983 --> 00:39:42,542
h-he's not opening. What now?

653
00:39:42,943 --> 00:39:44,463
Is he even inside?

654
00:39:44,622 --> 00:39:45,262
Yes.

655
00:39:45,423 --> 00:39:47,102
My friend saw him come back today.

656
00:39:47,102 --> 00:39:48,222
He's definitely home now.

657
00:39:50,702 --> 00:39:51,262
Pry it.

658
00:39:51,262 --> 00:39:51,903
Okay.

659
00:39:53,062 --> 00:39:53,863
Pry it.

660
00:39:54,023 --> 00:39:56,463
I told you to pry it! Pry the door!

661
00:39:57,582 --> 00:39:58,383
Okay, okay.

662
00:39:59,463 --> 00:39:59,983
Sir.

663
00:40:16,903 --> 00:40:19,823
What was this Uncle Bo of yours
doing this morning?

664
00:40:19,903 --> 00:40:21,662
Uncle Bo was at the company
the whole time.

665
00:40:22,622 --> 00:40:26,222
He sent us to cooperate with your work.

666
00:40:27,622 --> 00:40:30,142
This definitely has nothing
to do with Uncle Bo.

667
00:40:30,383 --> 00:40:33,463
No way. It's only 100,000.

668
00:40:33,943 --> 00:40:34,903
I'm telling you.

669
00:40:35,182 --> 00:40:37,023
You're involved
in illegal debt collection.

670
00:40:37,222 --> 00:40:39,343
We'll need you to cooperate later.

671
00:40:45,622 --> 00:40:46,622
Who is Uncle Bo?

672
00:40:48,182 --> 00:40:50,622
Uncle Bo's real name is Lv Haibo.

673
00:40:51,222 --> 00:40:52,222
In his fifties.

674
00:40:52,423 --> 00:40:53,742
About 1.7 meters tall.

675
00:40:54,423 --> 00:40:58,142
He runs a loan company.

676
00:40:59,222 --> 00:41:01,343
About a month ago,

677
00:41:01,702 --> 00:41:03,742
Zhao Heizi borrowed
100,000 yuan from him.

678
00:41:03,983 --> 00:41:05,262
He still hasn't paid it back.

679
00:41:05,823 --> 00:41:08,142
Yesterday, I heard from my friend

680
00:41:08,503 --> 00:41:11,662
that Zhao Heizi won 150,000 in cash
at another card game.

681
00:41:12,222 --> 00:41:14,582
Since I knew he owed Uncle Bo money,

682
00:41:14,863 --> 00:41:17,503
I thought I'd help Uncle Bo
get the money back.

683
00:41:17,943 --> 00:41:20,823
By the rules, I get a 10% commission.

684
00:41:22,062 --> 00:41:23,343
Did Zhao Heizi have enemies?

685
00:41:24,182 --> 00:41:26,142
I really don't know about it.

686
00:41:26,903 --> 00:41:28,742
He owed money to a lot of people.

687
00:41:29,222 --> 00:41:30,943
And he hung out
with all sorts of people.

688
00:41:31,343 --> 00:41:33,542
Uncle Bo is the only one I know about.

689
00:41:34,903 --> 00:41:39,423
So, do you think
Lv Haibo is involved in this?

690
00:41:41,943 --> 00:41:43,503
I think it's unlikely.

691
00:41:43,903 --> 00:41:45,983
Uncle Bo has over a dozen guys
working for him.

692
00:41:46,142 --> 00:41:47,503
And he's so rich.

693
00:41:47,783 --> 00:41:51,423
Killing someone over 100,000 yuan?
Probably not worth it for him.

694
00:41:53,303 --> 00:41:54,423
So who do you think it was?

695
00:41:55,903 --> 00:42:00,983
I think maybe after he won
that 150,000 at cards,

696
00:42:02,102 --> 00:42:03,343
he got targeted.

697
00:42:03,343 --> 00:42:05,702
Then someone broke in,
killed him, and robbed him.

698
00:42:06,702 --> 00:42:08,542
Do you know where he won the money?

699
00:42:08,903 --> 00:42:09,542
Yes.

700
00:42:09,742 --> 00:42:11,062
Not just the location,

701
00:42:11,062 --> 00:42:12,383
I can even find out

702
00:42:12,383 --> 00:42:13,783
how many people were there.

703
00:42:19,329 --> 00:42:22,822
♪Replacing the weight of tears
with that of sweat♪

704
00:42:26,616 --> 00:42:31,937
♪Covering the gunshot's sound
with wounds♪

705
00:42:34,010 --> 00:42:38,864
♪No one is born unyielding and strong♪

706
00:42:39,670 --> 00:42:42,817
♪But because someone
always rushes ahead♪

707
00:42:42,817 --> 00:42:45,921
♪To shield us from the storm♪

708
00:42:48,577 --> 00:42:53,711
♪When every extraordinary act
becomes routine♪

709
00:42:55,681 --> 00:43:01,313
♪Just to polish the badge
upon their shoulder♪

710
00:43:03,073 --> 00:43:06,657
♪Like light surging unseen
through the night♪

711
00:43:07,809 --> 00:43:15,249
♪Converging into your form♪

712
00:43:15,681 --> 00:43:18,359
♪Looking up♪

713
00:43:18,359 --> 00:43:21,898
♪Such dazzling glory♪

714
00:43:22,881 --> 00:43:25,441
♪Like hope♪

715
00:43:25,441 --> 00:43:29,374
♪Reaching out its arms♪

716
00:43:30,241 --> 00:43:32,893
♪Cloaked in light♪

717
00:43:32,893 --> 00:43:37,377
♪Alone, they charge ahead♪

718
00:43:37,377 --> 00:43:40,193
♪Traversing♪

719
00:43:40,193 --> 00:43:46,704
♪The battlefield of fate♪
